<Link id="l00067" /><CodeLine lineNumber="67"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// function to support it correctly.</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02012" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2012"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Use this to get a StringMap to all registered named options</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02013" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2013"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// (e.g. -help).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02014" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2014"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02015" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2015"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\return A reference to the StringMap used by the cl APIs to parse options.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02016" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2016"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02017" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2017"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Access to unnamed arguments (i.e. positional) are not provided because</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02018" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2018"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// it is expected that the client already has access to these.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02019" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2019"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02020" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2020"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Typical usage:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02021" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2021"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\code</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02022" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2022"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// main(int argc,char&#42; argv&#91;&#93;) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02023" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2023"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// StringMap&lt;llvm::cl::Option&#42;&gt; &amp;opts = llvm::cl::getRegisteredOptions();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02024" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2024"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// assert(opts.count(&quot;help&quot;) == 1)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02025" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2025"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// opts&#91;&quot;help&quot;&#93;-&gt;setDescription(&quot;Show alphabetical help information&quot;)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02026" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2026"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// // More code</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02027" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2027"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// llvm::cl::ParseCommandLineOptions(argc,argv);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02028" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2028"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// //More code</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02029" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2029"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02030" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2030"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\endcode</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02031" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2031"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02032" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2032"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// This interface is useful for modifying options in libraries that are out of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02033" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2033"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the control of the client. The options should be modified before calling</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02034" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2034"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// llvm::cl::ParseCommandLineOptions().</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02035" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2035"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02036" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2036"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Hopefully this API can be deprecated soon. Any situation where options need</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02037" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2037"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// to be modified by tools or libraries should be handled by sane APIs rather</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02038" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2038"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// than just handing around a global list.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02039" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2039"><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringmap">StringMap&lt;Option &#42;&gt;</a> &amp;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02068" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2068"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Tokenizes a command line that can contain escapes and quotes.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02069" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2069"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02070" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2070"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The quoting rules match those used by GCC and other tools that use</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02071" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2071"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// libiberty&#39;s buildargv() or expandargv() utilities, and do not match bash.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02072" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2072"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// They differ from buildargv() on treatment of backslashes that do not escape</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02073" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2073"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// a special character to make it possible to accept most Windows file paths.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02074" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2074"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02075" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2075"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\param &#91;in&#93; Source The string to be split on whitespace with quotes.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02076" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2076"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\param &#91;in&#93; Saver Delegates back to the caller for saving parsed strings.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02077" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2077"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\param &#91;in&#93; MarkEOLs true if tokenizing a response file and you want end of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02078" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2078"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// lines and end of the response file to be marked with a nullptr string.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02079" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2079"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\param &#91;out&#93; NewArgv All parsed strings are appended to NewArgv.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02080" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2080"><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/cl/#aff28c3d477d3a7870ec643381f186ed4">TokenizeGNUCommandLine</a>(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> Source, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringsaver">StringSaver</a> &amp;Saver,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02081" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2081"><span class="doxyHighlight">                            <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl">SmallVectorImpl&lt;const char &#42;&gt;</a> &amp;NewArgv,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02082" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2082"><span class="doxyHighlight">                            </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> MarkEOLs = </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">false</span><span class="doxyHighlight">);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02083" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2083"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02084" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2084"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Tokenizes a string of Windows command line arguments, which may contain</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02085" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2085"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// quotes and escaped quotes.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02086" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2086"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
